                        text "Tier E verified — no code change warranted. Each item confirmed benign:\n- E3a apply_med_set_align_symbol / E3b cmatrix_init / E3c fsm_context_restrict: the \"leaks\" don't exist in the port. align_symbol (Option<String>) and confusion_matrix (Vec) drop their old value on reassignment; fsm_context_restrict does drop(lr). Owned data frees automatically.\n- E5 iface print_dot: already uses vec![0i16; linecount] — the C sizeof(POINTER) over-allocation is not reproduced.\n- E6 lexcread suffix-merge: the index-chain Vecs drop at scope end; no leak.\n- E1 minimize inv_t_count: the folded-false comparison only picks which splitter block skips the symloop-from-zero mark — a Hopcroft ordering heuristic. Hopcroft is confluent, so the minimal DFA is identical regardless. Output unchanged; fix is zero-benefit churn on delicate core code.\n- E2 determinize nhash_load: undercounting only delays a rehash (bucket regrow); the determinized net is identical. Output unchanged.\n- E4 apply_index final-block: the last state is left unindexed and served by the correct linear/binary search fallback. Output unchanged; indexing is a pure speed optimization.\nConclusion: 3 already-correct-in-Rust (owned Drop), 1 correct sizing, 2 correct fallback; the 3 core-algorithm heuristics (E1/E2/E4) have identical observable output. Changing minimize/determinize/apply internals for no observable benefit adds risk with no upside, so closed as verified-benign per the tier's verify-then-tidy intent. The code comments already document each as a kept C quirk."
                    }

