                    {
                        at 2026-07-08T16:43:02.403336Z
                        author "brendan@necessary.nu"
                        kind @decision
                        text "SCOPED + designed, not started (atomic change too large to land green safely at the tail of this session; a half-done threading breaks the build because a threaded &mut Session and any remaining global-backed stack call operate on DIFFERENT stacks — no per-file incrementalism possible).\n\nVerified scope (corrected: the earlier \"475\" was int_stack_* matching stack_*): the network stack is CLI-ONLY — 0 library calls; 100% funnelled through 18 wrapper fns in stack.rs; MAIN_STACK/ARENA never touched outside stack.rs. Real threading surface: ~197 non-test iface call sites, 260 iface test sites (64 tests, 58 direct stack_init, NOT funnelled through one helper), 13 bin sites, ~100 iface_* fns, + regex.rs (1 site). int_stack/ptr_stack are library algorithm-scratch (0 CLI calls) — a SEPARATE later concern, become owned structs, NOT Session.\n\nDesign (Option A — explicit threading, for re-entrancy/embeddability):\n1. stack.rs: `pub struct Session { main_stack: Option<usize>, arena: Vec<StackEntry> }` (+ options/defines in later tiers). Move MAIN_STACK/ARENA into fields. Convert the private helpers (main_stack(), e_next/e_number/e_previous/set_*, arena_alloc(_sentinel), walk_to_top, take_fsm/ah/amedh) and the 18 public fns (stack_init/add/pop/size/isempty/clear/rotate/turn/find_top/bottom/second/get_ah/get_med_ah/print + the 4 entry accessors stack_entry_fsm/ah/amedh/next) into `impl Session` methods (&self / &mut self). Session::new() creates an initialised empty stack.\n2. Every `pub fn iface_*` gains `session: &mut Session` as first param; body `stack_X(..)` -> `session.stack_X(..)`; nested iface_* calls thread `session`.\n3. bin/foma.rs: create `let mut session = Session::new();` in main; dispatch(line, &mut session) + the 3 helpers (try_zero_arg/try_print_family/try_test) take it; the 112 dispatch call sites pass it. flookup/cgflookup don't use the stack (standalone) — no change beyond any shared iface calls (they use apply directly).\n4. iface tests: each of the 64 tests gets `let mut session = Session::new();`; shared helpers push/push_topsorted/top_is/etc. take `&mut Session`; thread through all 240 stack_/iface_ calls. This is the bulk of the churn.\n5. Remove the MAIN_STACK/ARENA thread_locals + the free-fn facade; stack.md rule bodies note the file-static→Session change (the `main_stack becomes thread_local` notes get rewritten). No version bump if observable behaviour is unchanged (it is — same stack semantics), but the impl annotations move onto the methods.\n\nThen Tier 2 (options) adds G_* fields to Session (cascade: fsm_minimize reads G_MINIMAL/hopcroft — pass as params or Session ref; io G_ATT_EPSILON; lexc G_LEXC_ALIGN); Tier 3 (defines) adds defines/defines_f to Session (fsm_parse_regex already takes the defines param — just swap the ~21 iface/lexc thread_local reads for session.defines).\n\nEstimated ~1500-2500 LOC for Tier 1 alone. Best executed as a dedicated focused pass with fresh budget; the mechanical parts (signature + call-prefix rewrites) are scriptable per file, but the 64-test threading is fiddly and the whole tier must compile atomically."
                    }

